 and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13599] included only 
``*.nu``
 files in the vendor autoload
WindSoilder 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13605] made 
``ls -lf``
 output full path in symbolic target
 and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13553] added support for SyntaxShape::OneOf in named args
ysthakur 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13595] implemented parse time type checking for range
weirdan 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13631] dropped outdated 
``touch -d``
 example
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13628] removed unused 
``fs_extra``
 and 
``hamcrest2``
 dependencies
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13610] added fallback to extension-based content type detection when parsing 
``Content-Type``
 header fails
ayax79 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13624] incremented the eager dataframe cache value before returning it
qfel 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13618] preferred process name over executable path
 and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13596] fixed handling of spaces in executable names
devyn 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13597] added 
``--raw``
 switch to 
``print``
 for binary data
 and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13585] added parse error for external commands used in assignment without caret
Aakash788 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13600] fixed: Only home dir path in pwd will be replaced with 
``~``
 in titlebar
playdohface 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13589] made error-message more helpful when user invokes a non-executable file (#13477)
